Wash and dry produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens. Trim and thinly slice @cremini mushrooms{4%oz}(thinly sliced) (skip if your mushrooms are pre-sliced!).

Heat a drizzle of @cooking oil{} in a small #pot{} over medium-high heat (medium pot for 4 servings). Add scallion whites and cook, stirring, until softened, ~{30-60%seconds}.

Stir in @jasmine rice{1/2%cup} and 3/4 cup water (1 1/2 cups for 4); bring to a boil. Once boiling, cover and reduce to a low simmer. Cook until rice is tender, ~{15-18%minutes}. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

While rice cooks, heat a drizzle of oil in a large, preferably nonstick, pan over medium-high heat. Add mushrooms, @shredded carrots{4%oz}, a pinch of @salt{} and @pepper{}, and as many @chili flakes{1%tsp} as you like. Cook, stirring occasionally, until veggies are browned and mushrooms are slightly crispy, ~{5-6%minutes}.

Add @sesame seeds{1%tbsp} and cook, stirring, until lightly golden and fragrant, ~{1-2%minutes} more. Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

Open package of @shrimp{10%oz} and drain off any excess liquid; season with a large pinch of salt and pepper.

> Rinse shrimp under cold water, then pat dry with paper towels. Swap in shrimp for chicken.

Heat a drizzle of oil in pan used for veggies over medium-high heat. Add shrimp in a single layer; cook, stirring occasionally, until browned and cooked through, ~{4-6%minutes}.

Meanwhile, in a small #bowl{}, whisk together @sweet soy glaze{4%tbsp}, @Sriracha{1%tsp}, half the @cornstarch{1%tbsp}, and 1/3 cup water (all the cornstarch and 2/3 cup water for 4 servings).

Once shrimp is done cooking, reduce heat to low and add sauce mixture. Cook, stirring, until sauce has thickened and shrimp is well coated, ~{1-2%minutes}. Remove pan from heat and stir in @butter{1%tbsp}.

Fluff rice with a #fork{}; gently stir in veggies and @sesame oil{1/4%tsp}. (Be sure to measure sesame oil—we sent more!) Taste and season with @salt{} if desired.

Divide rice between #bowls{} and top with shrimp and any sauce from pan. Garnish with scallion greens and serve.

> Shellfish is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 145°.